Literature Review: Swimming in complex fluids is a complex and dynamic phenomenon that has garnered significant attention in recent years. The study of swimming in complex fluids has far-reaching implications for our understanding of biological systems, soft matter, and active matter. In this review, we will classify swimming in complex fluids into eight distinct system types, each with its unique characteristics and challenges. We will provide a background for each system type and describe modern research findings, highlighting the current state of knowledge in this field.
